    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks attached to either end of a string that passes over a pulley. The pulley is located at the right edge of a table’s surface. One block is on the horizontal surface of the table, attached to the horizontal portion of the string, and has mass M sub 0. The other block hangs off the vertical portion of the string and has mass labeled “M sub 0 or 3 M sub 0”.\" src=\"/images/82819b96b8ed217036f19b8a1a361545.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is on a horizontal surface and attached by a string to a hanging block, also of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. Friction between the block and the horizontal surface is negligible. The masses of the string and pulley are negligible, and the pulley can rotate with negligible friction around its axle. When the hanging block is released, it has an acceleration of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. A second trial is performed after replacing the hanging block with a different block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"3 M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. The hanging block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"3 M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> has an acceleration of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> after being released. What is the ratio <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator a sub 2, and denominator a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator a sub 2, and denominator a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
